# Description
# -----------

#    This Singularity definition file builds a Singularity image
#    containing the following packages.

#    - Ubuntu 20.08 base Linux image;

#    - Miniconda Python 3.9+ stack;

#    - ufs_pyutils applications;

#    - rocoto applications (https://github.com/christopherwharrop/rocoto).

# Singularity Instructions
# ------------------------

#    To build the respective Singularity image file (i.e., container),
#    do as follows.

#    user@host:$ singularity build ubuntu20.04-miniconda-ufs_pyutils.rocoto_<TAG>.sif ubuntu20.04-miniconda-ufs_pyutils.rocoto.def

#    In order to execute and application within the Singularity
#    container, do as follows.

#    user@host:$ singularity exec ubuntu20.04-miniconda-ufs_pyutils.rocoto_<TAG>.sif <X> <Y>

#    where <X> is an executable or application within the Singularity
#    container (e.g., Python) and <Y> is an application exist on the
#    local host disk (i.e., a Python script/application).

# Author(s)
# ---------

#    Henry R. Winterbottom; 03 February 2023 

# History
# -------

#    2023-02-03: Henry R. Winterbottom -- Initial implementation.

# Base Image Attributes
# ---------------------

#    Image and Tag: noaaufsrnr/ubuntu20.04-miniconda-ufs_pyutils.rocoto:latest

# Container Image Downloads
# -------------------------

#    Sylabs: singularity pull library://noaaufsrnr/noaaufsrnr/ubuntu20.04-miniconda_ufs_pyutils.rocoto_tools:<TAG>

# ----

# Define the Singularity builder instructions.
Bootstrap: docker
From: noaaufsrnr/ubuntu20.04-miniconda-ufs_pyutils.rocoto:latest

%labels
    Author Henry R. Winterbottom
    Email henry.winterbottom@noaa.gov
    Version latest

%help
    The Singularity container application may be executed as follows:

    user@host: singularity exec ubuntu20.04-miniconda-ufs_pyutils.rocoto_<TAG>.sif <X> <Y>

    where <X> is an executable or application within the Singularity
    container (e.g., Python) and <Y> is an application exist on the
    local host disk (i.e., a Python script/application).